The paper discusses the use of probabilistic models in machine learning, specifically in generative models, and their limitations in performing causal queries. This topic falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and systems and control (cs.SY).
